nd deseeded","1 tsp mustard of choice","1 tsp chilli powder","1 tsp ground turmeric","½ tsp ground cinnamon","50 g tomato paste (reduced salt)","160 g Greek yoghurt","50 g lemon juice","40 g vegetable oil","8 - 12 chicken drumsticks"]},{"title":"Mint dressing","content":["200 g Greek yoghurt","60 g fresh mint leaves (1-2 bunches)","50 g brown onion","100 g fresh tomatoes, cut into halves","1 tsp salt flakes"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["60 g slivered almonds","5 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only"]}],"id":"r114667","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZnjUyghp38w\/XZQwciSXnWI\/AAAAAAAAcl4\/Bzqh_fgrbX8qm8eMqR_O4FP4eWJf66tOwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0__CGWfNvcCj7VkhSi.png","title":"Tandoori chicken","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"36 g","fat":"29.9 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"7.9 g","calories":"1890 kJ \/ 450 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, plastic wrap, baking paper, wire rack, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), sealable container, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Chicken can marinate in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours.","You can use chicken wings or marylands in this recipe (adjust cooking time as needed).","<strong>Tandoori cauliflower<\/strong>: Replace chicken with 1 cauliflower, cut into medium-sized florets. Make paste and marinate as per recipe. Reduce temperature to 160°C and bake for 40 minutes (160°C) until tender. Serve with mint dressing."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","1h 35m","8 portions"]}